description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to come and work in the Pharmacy Production unit at the Royal Free Hospital. We have recently completed a major refurbishment for our non-sterile and CIVAS suites and now have ambitious plans to grow our team and department. We are looking for a Lead Operational Pharmacist to join the team and work in our MHRA licensed Pharmacy Production unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to develop your management and Technical Services skills and deliver positive change in a GMP environment. The successful candidate will be expected to manage and develop the junior pharmacists working in production and support the overall management of the unit. If you fancy the challenge of an environment that is pushing the boundaries of patient care then please consider us for your next career move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate is required to be able to demonstrate the trust values, the responsibilities of the job description, person specification and have a strong technical services background. You will be a quality driven, dynamic self-starter who is motivated by innovation in Pharmaceutical Production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe you meet the criteria of the person specification and would like to join the Royal Free at this time, we would be interested in receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about working at the Royal Free please visit our website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Rahul Sheth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Deputy Production Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Rahul.Sheth@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0207 830 2282 ext 33112&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Available for calls and informal visits : Monday to Friday 9:00-5:21pm subject to availability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
